<h2 id="mktg-manager">
	Ad Operations Associate</h2>
<p>
	Do you want to work on extremely hard problems, surrounded by a smart, passionate team in a fast-paced start-up environment? Triggit is hiring.</p>
<p>
	Triggit, an online advertising technology company based in SOMA (San Francisco) is hiring an Account Analyst to join our accounts team.</p>
<p>
	The Platform Operations Manager will oversee all Triggit campaign activity, monitor platform performance, and be ultimately responsible for executing client plans. There will be opportunity and expectation for growth within the company.</p>
<p>
	<strong>What You&#39;ll Do all Day</strong><br />
	&bull; Lead Triggit RTB Platform operations<br />
	&bull; Monitor, analyze, and optimize campaigns to achieve campaign performance goals and maintain client satisfaction<br />
	&bull; Assist engineering to improve Platform performance<br />
	&bull; Carry out QA for campaigns and technical integrations<br />
	&bull; Whatever else is required to get the job done</p>
<p>
	<strong>Requirements</strong><br />
	&bull; Excel mastery; capable of uncovering meaningful insights from large data sets<br />
	&bull; Must be immediately comfortable with complex online interfaces<br />
	&bull; 1+ years of ad operations or account management preferred but not required<br />
	&bull; Hungry self-starter with a relentless work ethic who doesn&#39;t want or need to be micromanaged<br />
	&bull; Detail-obsessed with a habit of being excessively thorough<br />
	&bull; College degree with a solid GPA or equivalent work experience</p>
<p>
	<strong>To Apply:<br />
	Please submit a cover letter answering the following questions and resume to jobs@triggit.com.</strong></p>
<p>
	1) If you had unlimited access to data on any one subject in the world, what subject would you choose to explore and what would you seek to uncover using the data?</p>
<p>
	2) If you could invite any 3 people to a dinner party (past, present, or future), who would you invite and why?</p>
