<h2 id="mktg-manager">
	Operations Associate -&quot;Wearer of Many Hats&quot;</h2>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Do you wonder what it&rsquo;s like to work at tech start-up in San Francisco? Are you drawn to the idea of entrepreneurship and changing the world? Triggit is hiring.</p>
<p>
	Triggit is looking for a passionate entry-level self starter to join our growing team. As an operations associate you&#39;ll do a little bit of everything in helping Triggit grow.</p>
<p>
	We cherish individuals who are intelligent, curious and fiercely independent. We get excited about personalities that light up when discussing the merits of ideas and are always exploring the next angle, and the next layer. We hire people who want the opportunity to have a direct impact on the performance of our company, who take pride in their work, and at the end of the day, are always up for a little more fun.</p>
<p>
	<strong>What You&rsquo;ll do All Day: </strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		As Triggit&rsquo;s Operations Associate you&#39;ll also be our wearer of many hat and you&rsquo;ll be put to work across an array of tasks and projects:
		<ul>
			<li>
				You&rsquo;ll be our social media guru and build our identity on Facebook, Twitter, and our Blog</li>
			<li>
				You&#39;ll assist operations working in HR, A/R, and more</li>
			<li>
				You&#39;ll be called on to help Sales and Marketing source leads, build collateral, and research market trends</li>
			<li>
				You&rsquo;ll also have the opportunity to build Triggit things like a propriety lunch ordering schedule and execute on varied admin tasks throughout the day.</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>We Offer You: </strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		10-12 week contract-to-hire position with chance of full-time employment at end of term.</li>
	<li>
		Insight into the inner workings of a VC funded start-up</li>
	<li>
		Opportunity to engage with every level of the company &ndash; you&rsquo;ll have the chance to listen in on sales calls, learn about fundraising strategies and generally soak up knowledge from the inside out.</li>
	<li>
		You&rsquo;ll get your hands dirty and make a real contribution to moving Triggit forward.</li>
	<li>
		The opportunity to grow within the company based on commitment and dedication to our product, and our team.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>To Apply:</strong></p>
<p>
	Please write a Cover Letter (Essay) answering the following question:</p>
<p>
	<em>If you could invite any 3 people (past, present or future) to a dinner party who would you invite and why? </em></p>
<p>
	<em>If you had unlimited access to data on any one subject in the world, what subject would you choose to explore and what would you seek to discover with the data?</em></p>
<p>
	In your email, please also include your resume, college transcript and SAT scores.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Compensation</strong>:<br />
	Based on experience. Contract-To-Hire position w/competitive wage. Salary, 401(k), Equity, and Healthcare if and when a full time offer is extended.</p>
<p>
	<strong>About Triggit: </strong></p>
<p>
	Triggit is a venture-funded advertising technology start-up and a leader on the real-time advertising exchanges. Triggit was founded in 2006 and has an office in SOMA, San Francisco, CA. For additional information, pictures of our swanky start-up offices, and more visit Triggit Jobs.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Top 7 Reasons to Work at Triggit: </strong></p>
<p>
	1. We invent game-changing technologies and actually make money from them.<br />
	2. We are a team of passionate personalities who work hard, and play harder.<br />
	3. Breakfast and lunch are catered with food from local hipster restaurants and food carts like Chairman Bao. If you work through dinner, we&#39;ll pay for that too.<br />
	4. Shelves are stocked with snacks, the espresso machine is fancy, and the fridge will have beer you actually like.<br />
	5. Our offices are in SOMA, an easy bike ride from anywhere in the City, and a simple commute from East Bay or down South.<br />
	6. Our neighborhood bar is Zeitgeist, we celebrate there often after big wins or awesome product releases.<br />
	7. And yes, we even have a foosball table. We are that &#39;clich&eacute;&#39;.</p>
